float   -   remove element from the normal flow of a page, and position it to the left or right of its parent element

float: left;
float: right;

element will float all the way to the edge of its parent element. If there isnâ€™t a parent element, the floated element will then float all the way to the edge of the page.
the width of floated element is default to the width of the content within it

Clearing float
    clear: left;
    clear: right;
    clear: both;
    to clear float, applied to element appearing after floated element

Containing float
//clearfix

    .group:before,
    .group:after {
      content: "";
      display: table;
    }
    .group:after {
      clear: both;
    }
    .group {
      clear: both;
      *zoom: 1;
    }

set parent class as group

